1.title: Noah Gardenswartz
1.plot: Noah Gardenswartz talks about a recent jewelry-based life change, explains why he likes drugs and gambling, and discusses the challenges of being a teacher.

2.title: Ramon Rivas II
2.plot: Ramon Rivas II talks about spending time with his nieces and nephews, reveals why he has trouble with women and explains how he managed to survive on a budget in New York.

3.title: Joe Machi
3.plot: Joe Machi dissects Tom Brady's faulty logic, points out the one way in which he and Bill Gates are similar and imagines a new alternative to pharmacies.

4.title: Drew Michael
4.plot: Drew Michael brainstorms about how he'd like to resolve an argument with his girlfriend and explains how conservatives can be accidentally progressive.

5.title: Aparna Nancherla
5.plot: Aparna Nancherla talks about her struggles with depression and anxiety, tells a story about being catcalled and imagines the future of internet listicles.

6.title: Nate Fernald
6.plot: Nate Fernald describes his terrible week, divulges his various insecurities, shames a rude audience member and does a few impressions.

7.title: Ali Siddiq
7.plot: Ali Siddiq tells a story about his fiercely competitive daughter, faces the hard truth about his son and describes how living in a white neighborhood has changed him.

8.title: Cy Amundson
8.plot: Cy Amundson reveals the strange ways in which his obsessive-compulsive disorder manifests itself, explains why he loves to lie and describes how to diffuse an argument.

9.title: Emily Heller
9.plot: Emily Heller does some spot-on impressions, reveals the most annoying thing about her own brain and explains why she's happy being single.

10.title: Erik Bergstrom
10.plot: Erik Bergstrom opens up about his recent battle with cancer, reveals what ruined his last relationship and explains his issue with the Insane Clown Posse.

11.title: Martha Kelly
11.plot: Martha Kelly shares her opinions on animal rights, talks about her experience with getting sober and reads a letter from a deceased cat.

12.title: Nick Turner
12.plot: Nick Turner talks about his rescue dog, defines the term "soul mate" and reveals how he prefers to get the results of STD tests.

13.title: Mike Recine
13.plot: Mike Recine dreams about his ultimate comedy goal, explains why his girlfriend isn't suited for her job and reveals how his brother outsmarted the Special Olympics.

14.title: Jacqueline Novak
14.plot: Jacqueline Novak talks about the horror of the human body, her love of food, her biggest fear and the least sexual word in the English language.

15.title: Naomi Ekperigin
15.plot: Naomi Ekperigin explains why she's excited to marry a Jewish man, shares the scariest thing about moving in with her fiance and admits that she doesn't miss being single.

16.title: Ahmed Bharoocha
16.plot: Ahmed Bharoocha shares an embarrassing phobia, talks about his problems with religion and technology, and tells a story about his overly supportive father.

17.title: Matthew Broussard
17.plot: Matthew Broussard admits he looks like a villain, explains why college is basically a social experiment and reveals the least sexy thing you can say to a woman.

1.title: Liza Treyger
1.plot: Liza Treyger talks about her future as a party animal, the dangerous side effects of weird penises and how difficult it is for her to get laid because of her standards.

2.title: Hampton Yount
2.plot: Hampton Yount explains why he thinks that the Olympics are racist, reveals how to deal with conspiracy theorists and describes why he can't wait to get divorced.

3.title: Michelle Buteau
3.plot: Michelle Buteau reveals how she met her husband and explains what it's like to be married to a white European man.

4.title: Barry Rothbart
4.plot: Barry Rothbart explains how he knows when the day is over, talks about dealing with strange hecklers and describes the hardest act he's ever had to follow.

5.title: Brooks Wheelan
5.plot: Brooks Wheelan imagines what would happen if he panicked onstage, explains how he learned about the Internet and tells the story of a prank gone painfully awry.

6.title: Andy Woodhull
6.plot: Andy Woodhull describes the perks of marrying a single mom, getting lice from his stepchildren, female farts and the time his dog ate all his condoms.

7.title: Randy Liedtke
7.plot: Randy Liedtke takes a phone call, plays a voicemail, wonders how soon is too soon to eat pizza after someone dies and talks about his girlfriend, who may or may not be real.

8.title: Beth Stelling
8.plot: Beth Stelling describes the weird aspects of being a female comic, her mother's struggle with phone companies and why she loves "The Bachelor."

9.title: Sam Morril
9.plot: Sam Morril talks about what we should be teaching children, nonsensical homophobia, the repercussions of telling controversial jokes and surprise orgies.

10.title: Joe List
10.plot: Joe List discusses coping with anxiety in yoga class, aggressive sex, strange male-bonding rituals and his uncle's questionable babysitting methods.

11.title: Sean Donnelly
11.plot: Sean Donnelly acknowledges his looks, talks about why he has a hard time losing weight and reveals what marriage has taught him.

12.title: Phil Hanley
12.plot: The freshest stand-up gets the fresh new look it deserves. Watch today's best up-and-coming talent taking the stage in breakthrough sets--filmed live and exclusively for Comedy Central.

13.title: Tone Bell
13.plot: Tone Bell explains why he doesn't want to meet his cousin's baby, reveals why he can't smoke weed and tells a story about a bank that doesn't take cash.

14.title: Andrew Santino
14.plot: Andrew Santino translates bird mating calls, explains what you should never do in a bar bathroom and reveals why most traffic laws are stupid.
